`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- **Case-insensitive path collision**: `MiniMap.tsx` importing `"./minimap"` caused TypeScript to match the directory to the file itself (case-insensitively on macOS). Using `"./minimap/index"` (explicit path) in the barrel avoids this entirely.
- **Fog-of-war via fixed grid**: The snapshot always generates a `(2×VIEW_RADIUS+1)²` grid centered on the player chunk. Each position is colored if discovered (active in ECS or persisted in store), or fog otherwise. This is simpler and more predictable than sparse/dynamic bounds.
- **Auto-discovery as a side effect**: `readMinimapSnapshot()` calls `discoverChunk()` for every active `terrainChunk` entity it iterates — the minimap itself populates the fog-of-war store as a natural consequence of polling.
